From the machine start function it seems to read the config so can you try just stopping the podman machine updating the config to enable rosetta and starting the machine? The machine config is a json file inside this dir:`podman machine inspect --format {{.ConfigDir.Path}}` 

```go
func (a *AppleHVStubber) StartVM(mc *vmconfigs.MachineConfig) (func() error, func() error, error) {
	bl := mc.AppleHypervisor.Vfkit.VirtualMachine.Bootloader
	if bl == nil {
		return nil, nil, fmt.Errorf("unable to determine boot loader for this machine")
	}

	cfg, err := config.Default()
	if err != nil {
		return nil, nil, err
	}
	rosetta := cfg.Machine.Rosetta
	rosettaNew := rosetta
	if runtime.GOARCH == "arm64" {
		rosettaMC := mc.AppleHypervisor.Vfkit.Rosetta
		if rosettaMC != rosettaNew {
			mc.AppleHypervisor.Vfkit.Rosetta = rosettaNew
		}
	}
	return apple.StartGenericAppleVM(mc, vfkitCommand, bl, mc.AppleHypervisor.Vfkit.Endpoint)
}
```

If that doesn't work I suggest deleting the podman machine and creating a new one. From memory Rosetta needs to be installed, rosetta should be enabled by default, maybe the podman machine was created before Rosetta was installed on your system and that's causing an issue?

Note: Deleting the podman machine will delete all your podman resources.
